- AI detection tools have 15–30% error rates and 61.3% false positive rates for non-native English speakers
- "AI content" is a spectrum, not a binary classification
- Ranking position is only one metric; traffic, conversions, and AI citations matter equally in 2026</p>
<h2>Finding #1: AI Content Is Already the Majority &#123;#finding-1&#125;</h2>
<p><strong>86.5% of top-ranking pages contain some AI-generated content.</strong></p>
<p>This is the most important number in this entire study. It means AI is not an experiment anymore. It is the default production method for content that ranks.</p>
<p>The Ahrefs study of 600,000 pages broke this down further:</p>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
